      <h1 class='title'>Looked-after Children/Care Leavers</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 16 September 2004 vol 424 c1693WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_1693ws' title='Col. 1693WS &mdash; HC Deb 16 September 2004 vol 424 c1693WS' name='column_1693ws' href='#column_1693ws' rel='bookmark'>1693WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_252'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-annette-brooke' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_252' title='Link to this speech by Ms Annette Brooke' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-annette-brooke" title="Ms Annette Brooke">Mrs. Brooke</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">To ask the Secretary of State for Education and Skills what plans he has to extend the funding which was available for the purchase of capital equipment for looked-after children and care leavers in 2002&#x2013;03 and 2003&#x2013;04 to future years; and what plans there are for alternative funding. [188994]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_253'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-david-miliband' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_253' title='Link to this speech by Mr David Miliband' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-david-miliband" title="Mr David Miliband">Mr. Miliband</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para"> <span class="italic">[holding answer 14 September 2004]:</span> Overall support for capital investment in schools, including buildings and information and communications technology, has risen to &#x00A3;4.9 billion in 2004&#x2013;05, and will rise to &#x00A3;5.5 billion in 2005&#x2013;06. Increasingly, we provide this support direct to local authorities, and let them set priorities locally. Looked-after children can benefit from this investment, and we have no plans to extend the specific. Quality Protects Information Technology Grant, which ended in 2003&#x2013;04.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
